Install pip: 
$ python3 --version
$ sudo apt update
$ sudo apt install python3-pip
$ pip3 --version

Using PIP:
$ pip3 --help
$ pip3 search <keyword>
$ pip3 search vlc

$ pip3 install <package_name>


On Debian-derived Linux distributions (like Ubuntu and Mint), install PyAudio using APT: execute sudo apt-get install python-pyaudio python3-pyaudio in a terminal.

$ sudo apt-get install python3-pyaudio
or
$ sudo apt-get install portaudio19-dev
$ pip install ledfx

Launch LedFx with the open-ui option to launch the browser:
$ ledfx --open-ui

To check what directories are in your $PATH, you can use either the printenv or echo command:
$ echo $PATH

In this example, weâ€™ll set the variable in the ~/.bashrc file. Open the file with your text editor 

$ nano ~/.bashrc

and add the following line at the end of it:
export PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH"

Save the file and load the new $PATH into the current shell session using the source command:
$ source ~/.bashrc
